list.name: Default Changelist
list.comment: Tracking Text record types now - Priority Queue change types into Enum - Added edge case for aggregating

task.summary: Augmented Move Api and started support addition for ImageLinks - Augmented Move API with filters.

Bug fixes for POST /move GET /move - Fixed required parameter bug GET for /Moves - Null pointer fix for filter parameter when not used - POST changed cross-origins to direct web address - POST change bug where we were adding directly to object today's date vs. filling in with csv data, causing all records to display today's date on front end while CSV internally had the date record was recorded

Created "Aggregations" Endpoint - Fixed required parameter bug GET for /Moves, null pointer for filter, - Changed resource file name back (bug) from moves-old -> moves - Cached moveMap on initialization - Turned off commandline runner - should only be on during testing
Update to Aggregations - Requestbody replacing request params for list of requested move ids - Defined Aggregation type
Update to Aggregations - Requestbody replacing request params for list of requested move ids - Defined Aggregation type

Fixed Bug in data of CSV "moves" where values input was split, causing extra column - which threw off getting recordValue from row 5, since an extra column pushed it to row 6 so we received date instead
Added Filter by type ordering, grouping. Added support for Ritual type moves in ordering
Added Filter by type ordering, grouping. Added support for Ritual type moves in ordering - Ideally improve runtime needed for algorithms - Cleanup
Added Tags support - moves.csv contain move entries with tags
Adding new moves with tags (relax, eod, spartan)
Tracking Text record types now - Priority Queue change types into Enum - Added edge case for aggregating
Cleaned records of entries with extra commas - commas causing issues, need to remove them on user submission or before - tests needed for commas - added Condition enum
